frus:attachment.p:
If it was to be conducted properly and in an expert manner, the
                                    work before such a committee would be very onerous indeed, for
                                    it would embrace: 
                                        1.

The whole existing and past systems for the collection
                                            and application of revenues, internal as well as
                                            external;
                                        2.

The Liberian frontier force;
                                        3.

Railways, roads, and telegraphs;
                                        4.

Harbours, shipping, and coastal communications;
                                        5.

Agriculture;
